column9: The Echo Rockport TMDL indicated that this watershed had an outsized importance on the water quality of Echo Reservoir. A lot of NPS work has been completed, but there is still need for additional work.

This is a highly agricultural AU with extensive livestock grazing. The Echo Rockport TMDL identified it as an outsized source of nutrients into Echo Reservoir. Some NPS work has been completed in the watershed, and there are many additional opportunities.

Mostly undeveloped area, much of which is in the process of being purchased by summit county. There is extensive floodplain and stream restoration opportunity along the creek. Restoration work partially addresses the issues in the watershed, but doesn't address hydromodification in the headwaters.
Major development in this HUC threatens water quality. Hydromodification is a huge challenge.
Cluster of watersheds around Pineview Reservoir.
Cluster of watersheds around Pineview Reservoir

Two watersheds in the Pineview area lit up under this scenario. I placed them in the NPS bin, because any actions to reduce the impacts of climate change on temperature would likely include some combination of instream flows and restoration.
This watershed was in the lower left quadrant, but I'm including it to cluster with the remaining Pineview watersheds.
This watershed was in the lower left quadrant, but I'm including it to cluster with the remaining Pineview watersheds.

Hardscrabble Creek lights up as a watershed to protect in other analyses due to its general remoteness, and support for native fisheries. This would be a good watershed to focus protection efforts on. Activities such as land conservation and habitat reconnection would be appropriate projects.

The watersheds around East Canyon Reservoir were all highlighted under this scenario. Biasing towards high ecological value grouping them together in a watershed planning area would potentially make sense.
Looking heavily at ecological index with this scenario.
Lower Chalk Creek has been significantly altered by hydromodification.
Focusing mostly on ecological index. Both watersheds in East Canyon Creek pop out.
Pristine watershed, but water development risks threaten long-term water quality.
